<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1898,2033]" pageId="2" pageNumber="187">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,1899,1925]" pageId="2" pageNumber="187">Female.</emphasis>
Sternite VII with middle of posterior margin excavated and with M-shaped macula (
<figureCitation box="[1230,1321,1898,1925]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1854,1879]" captionTargetBox="[159,1435,568,1819]" captionTargetId="figure@1.[151,1436,558,1826]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Pascoia rakitovi Duan sp. n. A–C: habitus, dorsal view; D, E: habitus, lateral view; F, G: face; H: end of female abdomen, ventral view. A, B, D, F: male; C, E, G, H: female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3898076" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3898076/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="187">Figs 1H</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1333,1366,1899,1925]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1158,1183]" captionTargetBox="[162,1427,182,1124]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,181,1132]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pascoia rakitovi Duan sp. n. A: second valvula; B: detail of second valvula; C: first valvula; D: apex of first valvula; E: detail of first valvula; F: female sternite VII, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3898082" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3898082/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="187">4F</figureCitation>
). First valvula dorsal sculpturing granulose to maculose, extended to dorsal margin and merging with ventral sculptured area near apex (
<figureCitation box="[330,401,1970,1997]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1158,1183]" captionTargetBox="[162,1427,182,1124]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,181,1132]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pascoia rakitovi Duan sp. n. A: second valvula; B: detail of second valvula; C: first valvula; D: apex of first valvula; E: detail of first valvula; F: female sternite VII, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3898082" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3898082/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="187">Figs 4</figureCitation>
C–E). Second valvula slightly broadened to midlength then tapered to acuminate apex, with small obliquely triangular dorsal teeth over apical half (
<figureCitation box="[773,914,2006,2033]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1158,1183]" captionTargetBox="[162,1427,182,1124]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,181,1132]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pascoia rakitovi Duan sp. n. A: second valvula; B: detail of second valvula; C: first valvula; D: apex of first valvula; E: detail of first valvula; F: female sternite VII, ventral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3898082" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3898082/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="187">Figs 4A, 4B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
